name: national-wildlife-refuges-of-louisiana-utm-zone-15-nad83-usfws-2001-national-wildlife-refu-2001
notes: National Wildlife Refuges are federal lands managed by the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service (USFWS). The primary source for boundary information is the USFWS Realty program (status maps, legal surveys). An effort by the USFWS Region 4 (southeast states - AL, AR, FL, KY, GA, LA, MS, NC, SC, TN, PR, VI) Realty Division, Surveys and Maps Branch resulted in digital refuge boundaries for all refuges in the southeast at a scale of 1:24,000.
